@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "User Guide";
    Layout = "_ContentLayout";
}

<div class="container py-5">
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h2 class="section-header">Welcome to MapLab</h2>
        <p>Welcome to the MapLab User Guide! This guide is designed to provide you with a comprehensive understanding of how to navigate and utilize the MapLab platform effectively. MapLab is a powerful and user-friendly mapping application that allows users to create, customize, and share interactive maps with ease. Whether you're a casual user looking to visualize geographical data, a researcher organizing location-based information, or a professional working with maps, this guide will help you make the most of MapLab's features.</p>
        <p>Throughout this guide, we will cover key functionalities such as user authentication and roles, how to create and edit maps, different tools available for customization, and how to save and share your work. Additionally, we will explore the community-driven aspects of MapLab, including how users can engage with shared maps, discover popular content, and contribute to the platform. By following this guide, you will gain the knowledge needed to efficiently create and manage maps tailored to your specific needs.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h2 class="section-header">Home Page</h2>
        <p>Upon entering the website, users will be introduced to the main purpose and functionalities of the application. The navigation bar includes the following pages:</p>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Home</strong> – Provides an overview of the platform, its features, and how it can benefit users.</li>
            <li><strong>Community</strong> – Displays user-created maps, including the most popular, most liked, and top-rated maps over a certain period.</li>
            <li><strong>News</strong> – Covers platform updates, new features, events, and announcements about upcoming initiatives.</li>
        </ul>
        <img src="placeholder_homepage.jpg" alt="Homepage preview" />
    </section>
</div>
